        <updateDate>2021-04-23T14:53:19Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Emergency Savings Accounts Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill allows an individual taxpayer occupying a residence a deduction from gross income for up to $5,000 of amounts paid into such taxpayer's emergency savings account. The bill defines <i>emergency savings account</i> as an account established exclusively to pay the qualified disaster and public health emergency expenses of the account beneficiary. </p> <p>The bill defines <i>qualified disaster and public health emergency expenses</i> as disaster mitigation expenses, disaster recovery expenses, public health emergency expenses, and unemployment-related expenses.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
